content.description:
Smack in the middle of the Dubeck boulder is this fun yet short problem.  

  Start with a left hand on the lowest part of big sidepull and a right hand on sidepull down and right. Bump the left hand up and fire up and right to the arete. Follow the arete up.
content.location: Find the Dubeck boulder. Its right on the Caves Trail and is usually full of chalk.

content.description: Slap your way up the left arete of the Dubeck boulder.  Start low on a jug and go all the way to the top.
content.protection: a pad and a spotter to move it
content.location: The caves trail goes right past it, about 10 minutes (?) from the split off the hanger 18 - top rock trail.  Follow the cairns

content.description: A typical Haycock diabase route - start using an undercling at the base of the lip and slap your way up the lip then right top out in the center of the boulder
content.protection: 2-3 pads to cover the boulders below.
content.location: Follow the caves trail past Fluffy clouds for 10-15 minutes. Turn left when you get to the fork that has little fluffy on the right. Follow the stacks of rocks that people have marked for you, keep hopping and skipping, you'll need to go farther than you think.
